               <head>Grant; Needham-Street, etc.; 1323</head>
               <msContents><textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  <msItem>
                     <p>
                        <placeName key="place_111667">Needham-Street (Gazeley)</placeName>.
                        <origDate when="1323">1323</origDate>. 
                        Grant from <persName>
                           <forename>Walter</forename> 
                           <surname>Persoun</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_111667">Needham Street (Nedham)</placeName>
                        </persName> in the parish of <placeName key="place_111660">Gazeley (Gayslee)</placeName>, and <persName nymRef="Persoun">
                           <forename>Beatrice</forename>, his wife</persName>, to <persName>
                           <forename>Walter</forename> 
                           <surname>Priour</surname>
                        </persName> of the same, <persName nymRef="Priour">
                           <forename>Petronilla</forename> his wife</persName>, and <persName nymRef="Priour">
                           <forename>John</forename> their son</persName>, for a certain sum of money, of the homage and fealty of <persName>
                           <forename>Walter</forename> 
                           <surname>Clynckebelle</surname>
                        </persName> of the same, with his service of 9 d. a year, which he was wont to pay for tenements holden in the parish of Gayslee; viz. for a messuage in Nedham next to the messuage of <persName>
                           <forename>Maud</forename> 
                           <surname>Clynckebelle</surname></persName>; and for 1.5 acres of arable land, in two parcels, in a place called <placeName type="minor">Clynckebellescroftes</placeName>, both next tot he land of the said Maud.
                        Dated at <placeName role="date" key="place_111667">Needham Street (Nedham)</placeName>, on [19 June] Sunday before the feast of the Nativity of St John Baptist, 16 Edw. II [1323]
                        Witnesses: <persName>
                           <forename>Walter</forename> le <surname>Mercer</surname></persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>Robert</forename> de <surname>Hapetone</surname></persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>William</forename> 
                           <surname>Sperlyng</surname></persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>Robert</forename> 
                           <surname>(Smith) "Fabro"</surname></persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> 
                           <surname>Derson</surname></persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>Richard</forename> le <surname>Warner</surname></persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> 
                           <surname>Aumener</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_111667">Needham Street (Nedham)</placeName></persName>, and others.
                     The two seals are wanting.
                     </p>
                  </msItem>
